The Spring

     The river runs mad, untamed,
     plucking mountains into sails,
     while spring descends on meadows.

     Breezes fly lightly above,
     green and expanding,
     while bloom-rich air distills itself,
     bestowing rest upon purple hues.


- Marianne Moore
